<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Patenôtre</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">French
                                        Embassy</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-05"><hi rend="italic">June 5, 1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: The new note which you
                            have done me the honor to address me to-day, for transmission to the
                            Compagnie Française des Câbles Télégraphiques, reached me this evening.
                            I immediately sent a copy of it, as you requested, to the said company’s
                            representative at New York.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Patenôtre.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>